events.name: Introduction to Web Development
events.description:
Ever wondered how websites work and how they are built? Keen to create one from scratch? Register for our “Introduction to Web Development” session to learn more about what web development work entails. http://peatix.com/event/237091/ 



What You will Learn: - What are you seeing when you open your browser ?- What is data? - Intro of programming - How could you get started? 


Our Speakers: Sherwyn Goh Finance degree -> personal trainer -> Mexican burrito shop owner -> Software engineer + part time entrepreneur and coach Mito Qian Ye Mito is a restless explorer at heart, and a software engineer at Skyscanner - one who really cares about the product. If you can't find her coding at her desk, she's probably hunting for good food around the globe or punching/kicking off the guilty pleasures in gym. 


Note: Please bring your own laptop
events.location: IDA Labs Level 3 @ National Design Centre, 111 Middle Road, #03-04, 188969, Singapore
